If you want a high quality, accurate, reliable sidearm which will probably last for your lifetime and the lifetimes of your children, the H&K USP Compact will fill the bill. title: For Sale:  War Infantry Khukuri imported from Nepal - FREE SHIPPING
postcontent:
THIS KNIFE IS AWESOME!Hands down this is one of our favorite ever to come out of Nepal.
This design is known as the Ghurka Warrior's kukri.   It is similar to the Budhume which is the oldest style kukhuri.  The crafstmaship is amazing.
This particular style is very versatile: aside from the obvious wartime use it's often used for a variety of tasks from cleaning jungle brush and cutting bamboo to cutting vegetables and meat.
The blade on this khukuri measures 12 inches long and has 3 fullers.  The full tang is riveted to a 6.5" rosewood handle.  As with every Khukuri, this one comes with a set of Karda and Chakmak (high quality small utility knife and sharpener) as well as a buffalo hide covered cotton-wood sheath.The khukuri we offer are all authentic, hand crafted khukuri imported directly from Nepal.  Because they are hand made each will have slight variances and unique qualities.The blades are made from high grade carbon steel often taken from old railways or truck or jeep spring.  There's a reason these blades are famous for being indestructible! From the most basic design to the most decorated blade and sheath, all Khukuri are fully functional and built to last!Shipping is free to lower 48 states.  Alaska and Hawaii will incur an additional $5 shipping charge.  No international shipping is offered at this time.RETURNS:  Please inspect the knife immediatly upon arrival.  If there is a functional issue or the knife is damaged upon arrival we will accept a return for refund.  We will not accept returns on knives that have been used or mistreated.  You will be responsible for shipping the item back to us.  Return must be well packaged and shipped insured.FEEL FREE TO ASK ANY QUESTIONS.  I WILL ENTERTAIN OFFERS.
